President Obama had a call with President Lula of Brazil and Prime Minister Thomas of Grenada to discuss their efforts to achieve a positive outcome at the Copenhagen climate conference. President Obama emphasized the importance of working together to address climate change and highlighted Brazil's role in this effort. He also discussed the steps taken by the United States and his commitment to an agreement in Copenhagen that includes emissions reductions, financing, and a transparent compliance regime. The President also discussed the importance of creating a successful framework for emissions reductions and establishing suitable financing mechanisms and a transparent compliance regime.